# Environment Setup & First Spring Boot App

## What I Did

- Installed IntelliJ IDEA
- Installed JDK
- Created a new Spring Boot project
- Ran the application successfully
- Opened application in browser using:
  http://localhost:8080

## What I Learned

- What is an IDE (IntelliJ)
- What is JDK and why it is needed
- How to create a Spring Boot project
- What is Maven
- What is pom.xml
- How Spring Boot application starts

## Project Structure Explained

- src/main/java → main Java code
- src/main/resources → config files
- application.properties → application configuration
- pom.xml → dependencies and project info

## How Spring Boot Runs

- main() method runs
- Spring Boot starts embedded Tomcat server
- Application becomes ready to accept requests
